      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://assets.newatlas.com/dims4/default/bdc5f35/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1653x868+4+0/resize/1200x630!/quality/85/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnewatlas-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb7%2Faa%2F4aed5ebc4c08a4635b7ca9760b1e%2Fscreenshot-2026-07-03-at-9-13-44-pm.png&amp;rf.image_optimisation=0\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://assets.newatlas.com/dims4/default/bdc5f35/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1653x868+4+0/resize/1200x630!/quality/85/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnewatlas-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb7%2Faa%2F4aed5ebc4c08a4635b7ca9760b1e%2Fscreenshot-2026-07-03-at-9-13-44-pm.png&amp;rf.image_optimisation=0\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://assets.newatlas.com/dims4/default/bdc5f35/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1653x868+4+0/resize/1200x630!/quality/85/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnewatlas-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb7%2Faa%2F4aed5ebc4c08a4635b7ca9760b1e%2Fscreenshot-2026-07-03-at-9-13-44-pm.png&amp;rf.image_optimisation=0\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://assets.newatlas.com/dims4/default/bdc5f35/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1653x868+4+0/resize/1200x630!/quality/85/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnewatlas-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb7%2Faa%2F4aed5ebc4c08a4635b7ca9760b1e%2Fscreenshot-2026-07-03-at-9-13-44-pm.png&amp;rf.image_optimisation=0\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<p><img alt=\"A composite image of the M87* jet\" src=\"https://assets.newatlas.com/dims4/default/a36b94f/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1662x868+0+0/resize/1440x752!/format/webp/quality/85/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnewatlas-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb7%2Faa%2F4aed5ebc4c08a4635b7ca9760b1e%2Fscreenshot-2026-07-03-at-9-13-44-pm.png\" /><p>In April 2019, the Event Horizon Telescope (EHT) collaboration made history by releasing the first-ever image of a black hole – an object that, until then, had never been directly observed by humanity.</p><p><a hr